{
  "texts": [
    "Let us still prove the result for model (13) and for the operator Q p (f, f) only, which amounts to consider once again equation (64).",
    "The assumption that the integral operators K[f 1] and K[f 2] coincide almost everywhere obviously leads to a linearization of the model.",
    "Therefore, one deduces that the difference of two solutions f = f 1 -f 2 solves and satisfies initially f in (A, w) = 0 for a.e.",
    "A ∈ R and w ∈ I.",
    "We can then proceed as in the proof of Proposition 6, by considering again an increasing regularization of the sign function, depending on a parameter ϵ > 0, and using it to define an approximation |f | ϵ (t, A, w) of |f |(t, A, w)."
  ]
}